'''Tuck Muntarbhorn''' (Thai: ทัก มันตาภรณ์; born January 1994 in Bangkok, Thailand) is a Thai artist, curator, [[contemporary art]] collector <ref>{{cite web|last1=Dolciami|first1=Cristopher|title=TEDxSOAS Theme: "A New Perspective".|url=https://www.ted.com/tedx/events/21995|website=TED|publisher=TED|accessdate=5 August 2017}}</ref> and [[entrepreneur]] based in London and Bangkok.<ref name="auto1">{{cite news|last1=Cabasset|first1=Patrick|title=Grand Soir|url=http://www.styleconsulting.co.uk/press/tuck-muntarbhorn-in-lofficiel-paris-junejuly-2015-issue|accessdate=18 October 2016|issue=996|publisher=L'Officiel Paris|date=June–July 2015|ref=L 15003 - 996}}</ref> Muntarbhorn is Thailand’s first contemporary art collector to produce and curate an art exhibition in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tuck Muntarbhorn|url=http://www.aestheticamagazine.com/profile/tuck-muntarbhorn/|website=Aesthetica Magazine|publisher=Aesthetica Magazine|accessdate=5 August 2017}}</ref> He co-founded the international semi-couture brand [[Busardi]] in 2009 which presented collections during Paris Haute Couture Week.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dolciami|first1=Cristopher|title=TEDxSOAS Theme: "A New Perspective".|url=https://www.ted.com/tedx/events/21995|website=TED|publisher=TED|accessdate=5 August 2017}}</ref> Busardi is Thailand’s first brand to show at Paris Haute Couture Week.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pitchitmarn|first1=Parisa|title=DNA of Design|url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/print/739304/|accessdate=18 October 2016|publisher=Bangkok Post|date=22 October 2015}}</ref> Muntarbhorn views creativity as a spiritual practice: an awareness of thought, feeling, sensation, perception and intention; creating photography and sculpture to unite Eastern and Western symbols of [[spirituality]] to promote [[humanitarianism]].

